[COMPILING]:
            For compiling use Makefile:
            make

[INSTALL]:
           with root user:
           make install 

[USAGE]:
         dtraffic -i [interface] -m [mode]
         -i  <interface> indicate the interface to calculate the traffic rate
         -m  <mode> indicate the mode for scanning interface: [ down | up ]
         -l  Print the list of network interfaces
         -h  Print this help message.


[EXAMPLE]:
          dtraffic -i wlan0 -m down ---> scan wlan0 interface in download mode
          dtraffic -l               ---> print the list of network interface


[NOTE]: 
        version 0.9
